2.b The number of students applied for Data Science who knew Python and who didnt

In [20]:
DS=df[df['Areas of interest']=='Data Science ']
DSp=DS[DS['Programming Language Known other than Java (one major)']=='Python']
DSnp=DS[DS['Programming Language Known other than Java (one major)']!='Python']
DSnp['Programming Language Known other than Java (one major)']='Not Python'
DSp=DSp.append(DSnp)

Classification

1. K Nearest Neighbor(KNN)

In [356]:
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

preds=data_model[['Age','CGPA/ percentage','Expected Graduation-year','Rate your written communication skills [1-10]',
                  'Rate your verbal communication skills [1-10]','Degree Codes','Major/Area of Study Codes',
                  'Which year are you studying in Codes','Areas of interest Codes',
                  'Have you worked core Java Codes','Programming Language Known other than Java (one major) Codes',
                  'Have you worked on MySQL or Oracle database Codes','Have you studied OOP Concepts Codes']]
label=data_model['Label']

# Train/Test split: 70% Train and 30% Test Data 

X_train1,X_test1,y_train1,y_test1=train_test_split(preds,label,test_size=0.2,random_state=4)
print('Train Set: ',X_train1.shape,y_train1.shape)
print('Test Set: ',X_test1.shape,y_test1.shape)

Train Set:  (8000, 13) (8000,)
Test Set:  (2000, 13) (2000,)
In [357]:
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier

Ks=20
mean_acc1=np.zeros((Ks-1))
std_acc1=np.zeros((Ks-1))

from sklearn import metrics

# Finding best 'k'

for n in range(1,Ks):
    
    # Train and Predict
    
    neigh=KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=n).fit(X_train1,y_train1)
    yhat1=neigh.predict(X_test1)
    mean_acc1[n-1]=metrics.accuracy_score(y_test1,yhat1)
    std_acc1[n-1]=np.std(yhat1==y_test1)/np.sqrt(yhat1.shape[0])
    
print(mean_acc1)
print(std_acc1)

Train Set:  (7000, 13) (7000,)

In [367]:
# Finding best 'k'

k=10
mean_acc2=np.zeros((k-1))
std_acc2=np.zeros((k-1))

for n in range(1,k):
    
    # Train and Predict
    
    Tree=DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='entropy',max_depth=n)
    Tree.fit(X_train2,y_train2)
    Tree1=Tree.predict(X_test2)
    mean_acc2[n-1]=metrics.accuracy_score(y_test2,Tree1)
    std_acc2[n-1]=np.std(Tree1==y_test2)/np.sqrt(Tree1.shape[0])
    
print(mean_acc2)
print(std_acc2)

std_acc3=np.zeros((len(tech)))
